In Unit 4 you have learned about the rate of reaction. You have also studied the time 
taken for half of the reaction to be completed. However, some questions have not been answered yet. These questions include:  Do all reactions reach to completion? If not then how much of the reactants remain unreacted, that is, what is the extent of the reaction it took? Why does the reaction reach to completion? Why does it attain equilibrium? These questions can be answered after studying chemical equilibrium.
In this unit, you will learn about chemical equilibrium, how it is attained, and factors 
that affect the position of chemical equilibrium.
